  "label": "The Quadrant Grotto",
  "description": "The Quadrant Grotto is a deep cleft-cave driven into Orthant Crown’s shadowed facet, its walls formed from black crystal plates set at strict right angles. Vitreous ribs cross the chamber in a lattice-aligned grid, refracting Vesper Node’s meridian radiance into thin, immobile bands that never fully illuminate the floor. The interior surfaces bear stepped fracture-lines that repeat the massif’s four-faced geometry, turning sound and light into hard, measured echoes. A constant chill persists where laminar air-sheets slip through hairline seams in the prismatic rock.",
